  "body": "This test: https://github.com/ethereum/tests/blob/develop/StateTests/stSpecialTest.json#L2 has a transaction which costs only about 80k, but needs about 2GB of RAM and 18s in go.\nThe reason is the usage of a map to store JUMPDEST positions. In this test the code does 1024 recursive calls to itself. The code looks like: <1024 recursiv calls> STOP JUMPDEST JUMPDEST .... JUMPDEST (having 15k JUMPDESTS opcodes).\nCpp used a set for storing the JUMPDESTs, and needed 1.2 GB of RAM, we fixed it by using a vector of uint64_t instead (https://github.com/ethereum/cpp-ethereum/pull/2032), although this slightly reduces the performance.\nThis was found by a bug hunter through the bounty program. Gustav knows the details.\n",
