    "body": "This is fixed in the linked PR. It still uses a map, but keeps the JUMPDEST\nlocations around for use in recursive calls. The caching scheme keeps the memory usage\nlinear even for more complex scenarios involving multiple contracts. \n\nWith the fix in place, your test executes in about half a second and uses around 700k of memory for the jumpdest locations. \n",
